cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DS 

This paper discusses the study of malware and benign executables in groups to detect unknown malware with high accuracy. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also uses machine learning algorithms such as Random Forest, J48, LMT, FT, and NBT for classification, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of clustering algorithms such as k-Means, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the need for effective and efficient detection of malware in large amounts of executables, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
